{{Infobox football biography | name = Nathan Holland | fullname = Nathan Elliot Holland<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2017 |accessdate=26 September 2017}}</ref> | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|6|19|df=y}}<ref name="11v11">{{cite web |title=Nathan Holland |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/nathan-holland-254160/|publisher=11v11 |accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Wythenshawe]], England | height = | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] | clubnumber = 37 | youthyears1 = 2007–2016|youthclubs1 = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] | years1 = 2016–2017 |clubs1 = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] |caps1 = 0 |goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2017– |clubs2 = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] |caps2 = 0 |goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2014 | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-16 football team|England U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 | nationalteam2 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 15 | nationalgoals2 = 2 | nationalyears3 = 2015–2016 | nationalteam3 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 5 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2016 | nationalteam4 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] | nationalcaps4 = 2 | nationalgoals4 = 0 }} '''Nathan Elliot Holland''' (born 19 June 1998) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].
==Career== Holland was born in [[Manchester]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/who-is-nathan-holland-the-west-ham-winger-compared-to-ryan-giggs-and-steve-mcmanaman-a3473556.html|title=In Focus: Nathan Holland lays down an early marker at West Ham|publisher=|accessdate=20 September 2017}}</ref> A former [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] youth team player, he joined West Ham in January 2017 on a three-and-a-half year contract. He made his first team debut on 19 September 2017 in a [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] game against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] coming on as a 62nd-minute substitute for [[Sead Hakšabanović]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/teams/development-squad/squad/nathan-holland|title=Nathan Holland&nbsp;— West Ham United|website=www.whufc.com|accessdate=20 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41235277|title=West Ham United 3-0 Bolton Wanderers|date=19 September 2017|publisher=|accessdate=20 September 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
